from __future__ import annotations

"""
app/mme_scalpx/services/execution.py

Canonical execution service for ScalpX MME.

Frozen contract
---------------
This module OWNS:
- consumption of canonical strategy decisions
- publication of canonical ACK / order / trade-ledger outputs
- canonical execution state
- canonical position state
- execution singleton lock ownership
- sole position truth
- broker-order terminality for submitted execution intents

This module DOES NOT own:
- strategy generation
- risk truth
- monitor / report truth
- startup / composition logic
- alternate runtime roots

Design rules
------------
- execution = sole position truth
- risk may block entries but never exits
- pending execution must map to WAIT semantics upstream and must not be turned
  into degraded execution mode by itself
- entry orders that time out must be actively cancelled by execution
- names.py is the only symbolic source of truth
- redisx.py is the only transport façade
- main.py is the only startup root
- runtime entrypoint is exactly run(context)
- replay-safe and restart-safe

Important freeze correction
---------------------------
This rewrite consumes only the proven settings surface:
- settings.execution.idle_sleep_ms
- settings.execution.decision_block_ms
- settings.execution.lock_acquire_timeout_ms
- settings.runtime.heartbeat_ttl_ms
- settings.runtime.lock_ttl_ms
- settings.runtime.lock_refresh_interval_ms
- settings.redis.stream_maxlen_approx
- settings.startup.fail_fast

No guessed root-level execution_* settings are used.

Strategy wire correction
------------------------
strategy.py publishes the canonical decision wire as:
- decision_id
- ts_ns
- action
- reason_code
- entry_mode
- payload_json

payload_json contains StrategyDecision.to_dict(), and execution-specific order
details are carried in StrategyDecision.metadata. This service therefore reads
payload_json first and uses metadata as the canonical order-intent source.

Risk correction
---------------
Risk owns entry veto and max_new_lots governance. Execution must never widen
entry size beyond risk authority. On entries:
- if decision.quantity_lots > 0: lots = min(decision.quantity_lots, risk_cap)
- else: lots = risk_cap
"""

